# Portfolio front-end rules

You are a senior front-end developer working on a **Next.js 16** portfolio migrated from Adobe Portfolio. Follow user instructions precisely. Prefer readable, minimal diffs over clever abstractions.

See also `AGENTS.md` for Next.js 16 breaking changes ‚Äî check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when unsure about APIs.

## Project context

- **Stack:** Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, static project data in `src/content/projects/`
- **Visual parity:** Replicates isrrr.com; fonts are Google substitutes; scraped HTML lives in JSON blocks
- **Images:** Local under `public/images/` ‚Äî do not reintroduce `cdn.myportfolio.com` URLs
- **Structure:**
  - `src/components/layout/` ‚Äî Header, PageLayout, PageMasthead, BackToTop, SocialLinks
  - `src/components/project/` ‚Äî grid, cover, blocks, lightbox, embeds
  - `src/types/project.ts` ‚Äî shared `Project` / `ProjectBlock` types
  - `src/lib/projects.ts` ‚Äî data loading; `src/lib/blocks.ts` ‚Äî block helpers
  - `src/styles/project.css` ‚Äî styles for scraped `.project-html` content (imported by `globals.css`)

## Workflow

- Plan briefly for non-trivial changes; implement directly for small fixes ‚Äî no mandatory ‚Äúconfirm before code‚Äù step
- Fully implement requested functionality; no TODOs or placeholders
- Match existing naming, imports, and patterns in surrounding files
- Run `npm run build` after structural changes

