## Styling

- **New UI** (layout, header, components you author): use **Tailwind** utility classes
- **Scraped project HTML** (`.project-html`, tree columns, lightbox): keep rules in `src/styles/project.css` ‚Äî do not try to replace these with Tailwind; content comes from Adobe with inline styles
- Use CSS variables from `globals.css` (`--background`, `--text-primary`, `--text-muted`, font vars)
- Do not add shadcn/Radix unless explicitly requested

## TypeScript & React

- Use **semicolons** (matches `eslint-config-next` and the existing codebase)
- Prefer `const` arrow functions and explicit types for props
- Use **early returns** for readability
- This is **React**, not Svelte ‚Äî do not use `class:` directives or Svelte event syntax
- Prefer **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when hooks, browser APIs, or interactivity are required
- Client event handlers: name with **`handle` prefix** (e.g. `handleClick`, `handleKeyDown`)

## Accessibility

- Interactive elements: `aria-label`, keyboard support where appropriate
- Lightbox/dialog: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal`, Escape to close
- Images: meaningful `alt` text; decorative images use `alt=""`

## Content & assets

- Project metadata: edit in `/keystatic` or JSON under `src/content/project-meta/` and `src/content/homepage.json`
- Case-study bodies: `src/content/projects/` ‚Äî scrape with `python3 scripts/scrape.py`; do not edit blocks via Keystatic
- Adobe XD embeds: may die when Adobe access ends ‚Äî `ProjectEmbed` hides dead embeds; use `npm run prune-embeds` to remove from JSON permanently
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`)

## Commits (when user asks)

Use conventional commits: `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`

- `feat:` new feature ¬∑ `fix:` bug fix ¬∑ `refactor:` ¬∑ `chore:` ¬∑ `docs:` ¬∑ `style:`
- Imperative mood, no trailing period on subject line
- Only commit when explicitly requested
